commitResults.messageBody:
Single enum JunoType is used for referencing all types of command and
names in Juno

Not so sensible to use common JunoType enums for referencing both tasks
and errors using enums

Separating into enum JunoTaskType and JunoErrorType to handle types of
tasks and errors separately

commitResults.messageTitle: JunoUI.java : Add loadTasks() and add IOException catching
commitResults.messageBody:
No supported UI for task loading and no catching IOException that can be
thrown from task saving

Add loadTasks() to print relevant messages and call loadTasks() in
JunoTasks.java followed by showTasks() and catching relevant exceptions
Add IOException catching for methods that calls saveTasks() in JunoTasks

commitResults.messageTitle: Add toFileFormat() method for JunoTodo, JunoDeadline, JunoEvent
commitResults.messageBody:
They do not have method to yield appropriate format for saving

To save each task in text file, requires toFileFormat() method

Add toFileFormat() method to get task type, status and its description
as string supported for saving

commitResults.messageTitle: Add saveTasks() and loadTasks() method Add juno.txt under data Edit JunoException throwing details for each method
commitResults.messageBody:
Juno does not support saving current task list and loading it from
previous use

Add saveTasks() and loadTasks() to save task list under ./data/juno.txt
and load it from it while handling relevant exceptions

commitResults.messageTitle: Add overloaded getErrorMessage methods
commitResults.messageBody:
Single getErrorMessage method deals with all errors with different
conditions

Add four different getErrorMessage method to deal with respective errors
with different conditions

commitResults.messageTitle: Add abstract toFileFormat() method and fromFileFormat method
commitResults.messageBody:
Juno does not support retrieving appropriate task from saved text file

Add abstract toFileFormat() for subclasses to implement and fromFileFormat
method to retrieve task and return it to JunoTasks by line
